# Cloudflare Pages redirect rules — copied verbatim from public/ to
# dist/ at build time, then served by Cloudflare Pages. Syntax is
# Netlify-compatible:
#   from to [status] [!]
# where `*` is a wildcard, `:splat` references the matched portion,
# and `!` forces the redirect even when a matching file exists.
#
# Why these rules exist:
#   - Pre-fix the site had four URL forms per page (www vs apex,
#     trailing slash vs not). Google Search Console deduplicated them
#     via canonical tags but the report was noisy and the canonical
#     itself reflected the request URL, sometimes producing circular
#     refs. astro.config.mjs is now set to trailingSlash: 'never' so
#     builds emit `dist/contact.html` (no slash) instead of
#     `dist/contact/index.html` (slash). These redirects clean up
#     the old surface so previously-indexed trailing-slash URLs and
#     www-prefixed URLs collapse to the canonical apex+no-slash form.
#
# Domain canonicalization — www → apex
# Cloudflare Pages serves both www.perspectiv.net and perspectiv.net
# from the same project. We pick apex as the canonical host.
https://www.perspectiv.net/*  https://perspectiv.net/:splat  301

# Trailing-slash strip for the routes Google previously indexed at
# the with-slash form. Listed explicitly rather than via a wildcard
# so the rule set stays readable and routes that legitimately want
# a trailing slash (none currently) can opt out.
/about/      /about      301
/charter/    /charter    301
/contact/    /contact    301
/download/   /download   301
/pricing/    /pricing    301
